"{\"uid\": \"thetab.com-2024-07-31-erm-okay-so-what-on-earth-actually-are-the-paris-2024-olympics-mascots-the-phryges\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Genuinely thought they were supposed to be a poor imitation of the Eiffel Tower If you have watched any of the Paris 2024 Olympics, whether through TikToks, memes or *gasp* the actual TV, you will have almost certainly seen the slightly terrifying mascots, the Phryges.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 149, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TikToks\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a poor imitation\", \"from\": 43, \"to\": 59}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 79}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 130}, {\"ngram\": \"memes\", \"from\": 157, \"to\": 162}, {\"ngram\": \"*gasp\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 171}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual TV\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 186}, {\"ngram\": \"the slightly terrifying mascots\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 255}, {\"ngram\": \"the Phryges\", \"from\": 257, \"to\": 268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is already something slightly eerie about mascots in general, but what exactly are the mascots supposed to be?\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 387, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 297}, {\"ngram\": \"mascots\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"the mascots\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At first glance they look like a combination of a weird poo, crumpled Eiffel Tower and as one fan elegantly put it, \\\"a clitoris.\\\"\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"first glance\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"a combination\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"a weird poo\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 448}, {\"ngram\": \"Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"one fan\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"a clitoris\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's safe to say there is definitely nothing sexual about the Paris 2024 mascots, who play a key role during the Olympics and are actually called the Phryges.\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7575747479206836e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 567}, {\"ngram\": \"a key role\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"the Phryges\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reminded of the 2024 Olympic mascots and audibly groaned.\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic mascots\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\ude29pic.twitter.com/B7t94gRrRz - Busiris (@Busiris)April 2, 2024 The Phryges are actually based on the famous Phrygian cap, a symbol of freedom in France.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 851, \"end\": 863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phrygian cap\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 888, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9911294816479073, \"rank\": 0.005641587745355485, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\ud83d\\ude29pic.twitter.com/B7t94gRrRz - Busiris\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"@Busiris)April\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"The Phryges\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 814}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cap has been worn throughout major events in French history, most notably during the revolution where the cap became a symbol of a free republic.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The cap\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"major events\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"the revolution\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"the cap\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1024}, {\"ngram\": \"a free republic\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French National Archives show records of Phrygian caps worn during the construction of Paris' Notre-Dame cathedral in 1163, during the Revolution of 1789, during work to build the Eiffel Tower, and during the Paris 1924 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1057, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Archives_and_Records_Administration\", \"score\": 0.9999802878425007, \"rank\": 1.9691482661227007e-05, \"text\": \"National Archives\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Archives_and_Records_Administration\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Archives_and_Records_Administration\"}, {\"begin\": 1091, \"end\": 1099, \"