{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic Phryge\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"her emotions\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a mood.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"What a mood\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's ambassador to the UK has had a meeting - documented by official photos - with the Olympic mascots and there is not one thing about this I do not lovepic.twitter.com/0S9H8xY6c5 - Tom Hourigan (@TomHourigan)July 30, 2024 As for the Paralympic mascot, she \\\"hates being bored and loves to try new things.\\\"\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9911294816479073, \"rank\": 0.005641587745355485, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999969257239134, \"rank\": 3.054329576582238e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a meeting\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"official photos\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic mascots\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"one thing\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1744}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympic mascot\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"new things\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1919}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 president Tony Estanguet explained why they chose the caps to be their mascots, saying: \\\"We chose an ideal rather than an animal.\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1929, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7575747479206836e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1950, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the caps\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"their mascots\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"an ideal\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"an animal\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2067}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We chose the Phrygian cap because it's a very strong symbol for the French Republic.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2083, \"end\": 2095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phrygian cap\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 2145, \"end\": 2153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"score\": 0.9343454983882212, \"rank\": 0.06466024864837962, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very strong symbol\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For French people, it's a very well-known object that is a symbol of freedom, an object that will represent mascots all across the world.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2159, \"end\": 2172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"typ